# Kika, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Kika () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Pribaykalsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. As of the 2010 census, there was 508 people living There are 10 streets as of now.
Geography
Kika is located 48&nbsp;km northeast of Turuntayevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Turulevo is the nearest rural locality.
